Document: CodeHighlighter
Path: godot/classes/class_codehighlighter.rst
Summary: Provides syntax highlighting for code.

Inherits: RichTextEffect < Node < Object

This class is an abstract base class for creating custom syntax highlighters for the CodeEdit and RichTextLabel nodes. It provides a framework for defining how code should be parsed and styled based on its syntax.

To create a custom highlighter, you need to inherit from CodeHighlighter and implement the _process_code method. This method receives the text to be highlighted and should return a list of CodeHighlighter.Style objects, each defining a range of text and its corresponding style.

Key Rule: CodeHighlighter is an abstract base class and cannot be used directly. You must create a derived class to implement custom highlighting logic.
