Document: CodeHighlighter
Path: godot/classes/class_codehighlighter.rst
Summary: Defines methods for managing color regions, keywords, and member keywords within the CodeHighlighter class.

Method: add_color_region(start_key: String, end_key: String, color: Color, line_only: bool = false)
Adds a color region that spans from start_key to end_key, applying the specified color. If line_only is true, the region only applies to the current line.

Method: add_keyword_color(keyword: String, color: Color)
Adds a keyword and assigns it a specific color.

Method: add_member_keyword_color(member_keyword: String, color: Color)
Adds a member keyword and assigns it a specific color.

Method: clear_color_regions()
Removes all defined color regions.

Method: clear_keyword_colors()
Removes all defined keyword colors.

Method: clear_member_keyword_colors()
Removes all defined member keyword colors.

Method: get_keyword_color(keyword: String) → Color
Returns the color associated with the given keyword.

Method: get_member_keyword_color(member_keyword: String) → Color
Returns the color associated with the given member keyword.

Method: has_color_region(start_key: String) → bool
Checks if a color region starting with the specified key exists.

Method: has_keyword_color(keyword: String) → bool
Checks if a keyword with the specified name exists.

Method: has_member_keyword_color(member_keyword: String) → bool
Checks if a member keyword with the specified name exists.

Method: remove_color_region(start_key: String)
Removes a color region based on its starting key.

Method: remove_keyword_color(keyword: String)
Removes a keyword and its associated color.

Method: remove_member_keyword_color(member_keyword: String)
Removes a member keyword and its associated color.
