Document: CodeHighlighter
Path: godot/classes/class_codehighlighter.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and their corresponding setter/getter methods for the CodeHighlighter class in Godot Engine.

Property: color_regions (Dictionary)
Default: {}
Setter: set_color_regions(value: Dictionary)
Getter: get_color_regions() → Dictionary
Description: Sets the color regions. All existing regions will be removed. The Dictionary key is the region start and end key, separated by a space. The value is the region color.

Property: function_color (Color)
Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
Setter: set_function_color(value: Color)
Getter: get_function_color() → Color
Description: Sets color for functions. A function is a non-keyword string followed by a '('.

Property: keyword_colors (Dictionary)
Default: {}
Setter: set_keyword_colors(value: Dictionary)
Getter: get_keyword_colors() → Dictionary
Description: Sets the keyword colors. All existing keywords will be removed. The Dictionary key is the keyword. The value is the keyword color.

Property: member_keyword_colors (Dictionary)
Default: {}
Setter: set_member_keyword_colors(value: Dictionary)
Getter: get_member_keyword_colors() → Dictionary
Description: Sets the member keyword colors. All existing member keyword will be removed. The Dictionary key is the member keyword. The value is the member keyword color.

Property: member_variable_color (Color)
Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
Setter: set_member_variable_color(value: Color)
Getter: get_member_variable_color() → Color
Description: Sets color for member variables. A member variable is non-keyword, non-function string proceeded with a '.'.

Property: number_color (Color)
Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
Setter: set_number_color(value: Color)
Getter: get_number_color() → Color
Description: Sets the color for numbers.

Property: symbol_color (Color)
Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
Setter: set_symbol_color(value: Color)
Getter: get_symbol_color() → Color
Description: Sets the color for symbols.
